  "body": "I'm building a component that allows you to create social widgets. The problem I've run into is that by adding google plus and twitter buttons, they remove the react node id when I parse them using the Google Plus and Twitter API's. This makes perfect sense but if there was a way to ignore the fact that react can't find the node id, and just rerender the whole component in this situation, that would be great. Because the component live updates as you type in info, it gets an invariant violation and can't update the widget.\n\nHere's a little code in case you are confused.\n\n```\ncomponentDidUpdate:function(){\n    FB.XFBML.parse()\n    twttr.widgets.load()\n    gapi.plusone.go()\n    gapi.plus.go()\n    gapi.page.go()\n  },\n  componentDidMount:function(){\n    twttr.widgets.load()\n    FB.XFBML.parse()\n    gapi.plusone.go()\n    gapi.plus.go()\n    gapi.page.go()\n  },\n\n```\n\nThese functions remove the react node id's.\n\nThen when trying to update the twitter share button or anything else as the user types in information, it throws the error.\n",
